1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,280
A Kubernetes cluster has two sides.

2
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:08,940
The control plane that thinks, and the nodes that do.

3
00:00:08,940 --> 00:00:11,300
The control plane manages.

4
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:13,780
Worker nodes run your workloads.

5
00:00:13,780 --> 00:00:14,780
Five components.

6
00:00:14,780 --> 00:00:16,860
First, KubeAPER server.

7
00:00:16,860 --> 00:00:17,980
The front door.

8
00:00:17,980 --> 00:00:20,140
All API traffic goes here.

9
00:00:20,140 --> 00:00:22,540
It scales horizontally.

10
00:00:22,540 --> 00:00:23,540
Second, ECT.

11
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:24,540
The database.

12
00:00:24,540 --> 00:00:26,220
All cluster state lives here.

13
00:00:26,220 --> 00:00:27,220
Back it up.

14
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:29,280
Third, Kube scheduler.

15
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:32,160
Watches for new pods with no assigned node.

16
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:37,000
Picks the right one based on resources, constraints, affinity, deadlines.

17
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,440
Fourth, Kube controller manager.

18
00:00:39,440 --> 00:00:44,960
Runs controller processes, node, job, and point slice service account compiled into

19
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,600
one binary.

20
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,000
Watches for drift.

21
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Fixes it.

22
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,400
Fifth, Cloud controller manager.

23
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,280
Cloud integrations only.

24
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:56,320
Not present on-prem or local clusters.

25
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,880
On every node, three things.

26
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:04,240
KubeLit, the agent, ensures containers in a pod are running and healthy.

27
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:10,960
Kube Proxy, optional, implements service networking, can be replaced by network plugins.

28
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:16,760
Container runtime, containered, or CRIO, actually runs your containers.

29
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:19,560
Every cluster runs these pieces.

30
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:21,880
Now you know what they do.

31
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:25,240
Run the docs, Kubernetes cluster components.

